{"at": "2026-07-17T02:03:28.764730+00:00", "event_id": "01KXPX103WDRVR79963CEQW8GG", "event_type": "DecisionPointResolved", "payload": {"actual_participants": [], "closed_locally_while_widened": false, "closure_message": null, "decision_point_id": "01KXPWGMS4TSFYB0C5R24X6H9A", "final_answer": "The Standards & Security report's PWA checks (manifest, service worker) are presence-only booleans with no evidence, mixed into a flat check list. Issue #145 asks for a dedicated Progressive Web Resilience section reporting manifest characteristics, service-worker state, offline/network resilience, and installability as Pass/Fail/N/A with evidence \u2014 not another aggregate score.", "mission_id": "01KXPWGM126XQBHMF40TAH78W7", "mission_slug": "progressive-web-resilience", "mission_type": "software-dev", "origin_surface": "planning_interview", "other_answer": false, "rationale": "Derived from spec.md Problem/Goal sections, authored from issue #145 and a read of src/engines/standards.js.", "recorded_at": "2026-07-17T02:03:28.764730Z", "resolved_by": "mike.gifford@gmail.com", "run_id": "01KXPWGMS4TSFYB0C5R24X6H9A", "state_entered_at": "2026-07-17T02:03:28.760325Z", "summary": null, "terminal_outcome": "resolved"}}
