{"at": "2026-07-17T11:41:12.440309+00:00", "event_id": "01KXQY2VBREAMNP4DZ68TSJGT6", "event_type": "DecisionPointResolved", "payload": {"actual_participants": [], "closed_locally_while_widened": false, "closure_message": null, "decision_point_id": "01KXQY0VGGR04EQ3KCK3GY24EG", "final_answer": "Extend src/engines/standards.js's existing page.evaluate block to fetch/parse the manifest and expand service-worker state (IC-01, IC-02), add an origin-level memoized offline/network-resilience check in src/scan.js mirroring the existing runSecurity/runPublicInterest pattern with an isolated browser context (IC-03), derive installability from those outputs (IC-04), and restructure runStandards()'s return shape into a new resilience section migrated from the flat checks array, rendered as a distinct report subsection and threaded through the CSV/JSON API pipeline (IC-05).", "mission_id": "01KXPWGM126XQBHMF40TAH78W7", "mission_slug": "progressive-web-resilience-01KXPWGM", "mission_type": "software-dev", "origin_surface": "planning_interview", "other_answer": false, "rationale": "Derived from plan.md's Implementation Concern Map (IC-01..IC-05), grounded in research.md's D-01..D-06 decisions about scan.js's per-page vs per-origin execution model.", "recorded_at": "2026-07-17T11:41:12.440309Z", "resolved_by": "mike.gifford@gmail.com", "run_id": "01KXQY0VGGR04EQ3KCK3GY24EG", "state_entered_at": "2026-07-17T11:41:12.439169Z", "summary": null, "terminal_outcome": "resolved"}}
